description: NYT bestselling author. Attorney. Journalist. Twitter Verified, 10/2016‚Äì4/2023. Art critic. PROOF @ https://t.co/bGlpbdTQ7y; RETRO @ https://t.co/IArPG4otQC.
full_text: 23/ The media should say we live in such a politicized environment apparently no U.S. political party will stop a serial sexual assailant, traitor, criminal, liar, and election cheat either before or after they take office *if their voters decide they want that person in charge*.

description: NYT bestselling author. Attorney. Journalist. Twitter Verified, 10/2016‚Äì4/2023. Art critic. PROOF @ https://t.co/bGlpbdTQ7y; RETRO @ https://t.co/IArPG4otQC.
full_text: 24/ Then draw a bright red f*cking line between that political reality and whether or not America is going to have "rule of law." Because right now America has a choice: we can have a "highly politicized democratic environment" or we can have a damn autocracy. We can't have both.

description: NYT bestselling author. Attorney. Journalist. Twitter Verified, 10/2016‚Äì4/2023. Art critic. PROOF @ https://t.co/bGlpbdTQ7y; RETRO @ https://t.co/IArPG4otQC.
full_text: 25/ Every media segment on Trump-Russia should have two parts‚Äîthe length of each depending on the news of the day‚Äîa political analysis, which brings on political actors like Giuliani, and a legal analysis, which brings on legal and law enforcement experts. NEVER COMBINE THE TWO.

description: NYT bestselling author. Attorney. Journalist. Twitter Verified, 10/2016‚Äì4/2023. Art critic. PROOF @ https://t.co/bGlpbdTQ7y; RETRO @ https://t.co/IArPG4otQC.
full_text: 26/ Do *not* bring on any political guest‚Äî*ever*‚Äîto discuss the legal side of the case, else you help Trump establish RULE OF POLITICS over RULE OF LAW in America. All media questions should be either "political" or "legal" queries‚Äîno media question should ever commingle the two.

description: NYT bestselling author. Attorney. Journalist. Twitter Verified, 10/2016‚Äì4/2023. Art critic. PROOF @ https://t.co/bGlpbdTQ7y; RETRO @ https://t.co/IArPG4otQC.
full_text: 27/ If the media does this, we will come to understand that *no legal expert of any credibility* (and this excludes Dershowitz, who poisoned his analysis by being a Trump pal and advisor) believes the FBI and DOJ have treated Trump unfairly or that Trump is in good shape legally.

description: NYT bestselling author. Attorney. Journalist. Twitter Verified, 10/2016‚Äì4/2023. Art critic. PROOF @ https://t.co/bGlpbdTQ7y; RETRO @ https://t.co/IArPG4otQC.
full_text: 28/ By the same token, if the media does this, we will come to understand that the 2018 mid-term election is the most important election of our lifetime‚Äîas it will determine whether there continues to be a RULE OF LAW in America or whether political might is all that matters now.

description: NYT bestselling author. Attorney. Journalist. Twitter Verified, 10/2016‚Äì4/2023. Art critic. PROOF @ https://t.co/bGlpbdTQ7y; RETRO @ https://t.co/IArPG4otQC.
full_text: 29/ I'm a small-d democrat as well as a Democrat: I think if American voters know in advance someone is a traitor, criminal, liar, election cheat, and serial sexual assailant, they should be able to willfully destroy America by voting that cretin into the White House‚ÄîI really do.

description: NYT bestselling author. Attorney. Journalist. Twitter Verified, 10/2016‚Äì4/2023. Art critic. PROOF @ https://t.co/bGlpbdTQ7y; RETRO @ https://t.co/IArPG4otQC.
full_text: 30/ But I *don't* believe American voters can eliminate the RULE OF LAW without a Constitutional Convention or an armed rebellion‚Äîneither of which anyone wants. And I don't think either the media or law enforcement should help a candidate hide from voters who he is pre-election.
